<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,546,1075]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Shiny black; posterior margin of pronotum finely edged with orange-brown. Scutellum touched with two lateral spots and one apical spot, yellow. Forewings black with orange-brown spots.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,546,1075]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[199,372,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with rounded caudal margin. Subgenital plate obtusely produced laterally near base, caudal angle rounded, with short hair-like setae. Style with body almost of equal width, preapical lobe well developed, apical apophysis short, thumb-like. Connective with arms shorter than stem. Aedeagus short, stout, dorsal apodeme short and bilobed, preatrium not developed, shaft cylindrical, curved caudo-dorsally with dorsal keel (
<figureCitation box="[213,307,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 148–156" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[242,1352,213,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[194,1397,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 148–156. Penthimia neoattenuata sp. nov. 148. Male pygofer, lateral view; 149. Valve, ventral view; 150. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 151. Style, dorso-lateral view; 152–153. Aedeagus, lateral view; 154. Connective, dorsal view; 155–156.Aedeagus, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135506/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 152</figureCitation>
shown by arrow), gonopore apical on ventral surface, large.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,546,1075]" box="[199,490,798,823]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[199,284,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Length.</emphasis>
Male 3.8–4.0mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
